hands_on_practices.problem:
An endoscopic biopsy from the mid-esophagus shows stratified squamous epithelium without a macroscopic cornified surface. You are provided layer-specific immunohistochemistry (Immunohistochemistry, IHC) staining intensities for a panel of epithelial differentiation markers, scored on a $0$–$3$ scale where $0$ indicates no detectable staining and $3$ indicates maximal staining. Layers are defined operationally as basal (contacting the basement membrane), suprabasal (spinous/parabasal), and superficial (luminal). Cytokeratin (CK) designations follow conventional numbering. Choose the option that is most consistent with early keratinization in esophageal stratified squamous epithelium.

A. Basal keratin $5$/$14$ (CK5/CK14) strong in basal only ($3$);
non-keratinized differentiation keratin $4$/$13$ (CK4/CK13) reduced progression ($2$ suprabasal, $1$ superficial);
keratinization-associated keratin $1$/$10$ (CK1/CK10) newly present ($2$ suprabasal, $2$ superficial);
involucrin increased superficially ($2$);
loricrin detectable superficially ($1$);
simple-epithelium keratin $8$/$18$ (CK8/CK18) absent ($0$).

B. Basal keratin $5$/$14$ strong in basal only ($3$);
non-keratinized differentiation keratin $4$/$13$ robust across suprabasal and superficial layers ($3$/$3$);
keratinization-associated keratin $1$/$10$ absent ($0$);
involucrin low and limited to suprabasal ($1$);
loricrin absent ($0$);
simple-epithelium keratin $8$/$18$ absent ($0$).

C. Basal keratin $5$/$14$ strong in basal ($3$) and extended into suprabasal ($2$);
hyperproliferation-associated keratin $6$/$16$ (CK6/CK16) high in suprabasal ($3$);
non-keratinized differentiation keratin $4$/$13$ moderate ($2$ suprabasal, $2$ superficial);
keratinization-associated keratin $1$/$10$ absent ($0$);
involucrin low ($1$);
loricrin absent ($0$);
simple-epithelium keratin $8$/$18$ absent ($0$).

D. Simple-epithelium keratin $8$/$18$ strong across all layers ($3$);
basal keratin $5$/$14$ weak and limited to basal ($1$);
non-keratinized differentiation keratin $4$/$13$ absent ($0$);
keratinization-associated keratin $1$/$10$ absent ($0$);
involucrin absent ($0$);
loricrin absent ($0$).

Which immunoprofile most specifically indicates early keratinization of esophageal stratified squamous epithelium?
